# Glossary Term Completeness

When adding or updating glossary terms, preserve complete source information and avoid shortening or summarizing definitions.

## Requirements

- Do not summarize term text; include full term details from the source material.
- Include all relevant subterms under the parent term.
- Add aliases from the parent term to its subterms.
- Include parameterized subterm aliases where applicable (for example, `melee [value]`).

## Example: Melee

- Parent term: `melee`
- Required subterms:
  - `melee weapon`
  - `melee touch`
  - `melee [value]` (such as `melee 1`, `melee 2`, and so on)
- Expected behavior:
  - `melee` includes complete, unsummarized text.
  - `melee` aliases point to all listed subterms.
  - Subterm entries keep their complete wording and examples.
